  "text": "where λ > 0 is a regularization parameter that depends on and encourages sparsity. State-of-the-art CSC algorithms use ADMM to solve Eq. 9 [CITATION_1] . ADMM, however, is inherently an iterative algorithm that lacks the infrastructure that would enable the computation of the solution to Eq. 9 for all J examples in parallel. In section VI, we introduce an architecture that allows us to solve the CSC problem for all J examples in parallel using GPUs.",
